attributes.Transcription: Hello and welcome to our study. In front you  you will see a bathroom cabinet from IKEA.

attributes.Long form description: The student is disassembling a piece of furniture. He removes the wheels, unscrews the screws on the tray and the bars, and finally disassembles the base.

attributes.Transcription: Your task for now, will be to please disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first wheel of the furniture.
The student disassembles the screws of the middle tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should disassemble the middle shelf first.

attributes.Transcription: Before disassembling the top shelf, please disassemble the middle shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the upper grid tray.
The student disassembles the upper grid tray from the shelf.
The student disassembles the middle grid tray from the shelf.
The student disassembles the bottom grid tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should keep the frame stand on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Please use the key and cabinet horizontally put on the table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the base frame.
The student disassembles the screws on the right sidebar.

attributes.Transcription: Thank you very much. And it was everything for this task.
You can now press the stop button.
